 ] Verify error messages are clear\n963: \n964: **Verification**: All verification steps pass with no errors or warnings\n965: \n966: ---\n967: \n968: ## Summary\n969: \n970: **Total Tasks**: 71\n971: **Estimated Effort**: M (Medium) - 25-35 hours\n972: \n973: ### Key Deliverables\n974: 1. **Invoke Command** - CLI command with comprehensive options\n975: 2. **InvokeRuntime** - Core invoke orchestration logic\n976: 3. **Status Command** - CLI command for checking agent status\n977: 4. **StatusRuntime** - Core status checking logic\n978: 5. **HTTP Client Integration** - Async HTTP requests for invoke\n979: 6. **Provider Support** - Support for agentcube and k8s providers\n980: 7. **Comprehensive Tests** - Unit, integration, and E2E tests\n981: 8. **Documentation** - README, examples, and inline docs\n982: \n983: ### Success Criteria\n984: - All Python files compile without errors\n985: - All unit tests pass with >80% code coverage\n986: - All integration tests pass\n987: - All E2E tests pass\n988: - `agentcube invoke --help` displays comprehensive help\n989: - `agentcube status --help` displays comprehensive help\n990: - Invoke works with agentcube provider\n991: - Invoke works with k8s provider\n992: - Status works with agentcube provider\n993: - Status works with k8s provider\n994: - JSON payload validation works correctly\n995: - Header parsing works correctly\n996: - HTTP requests are made correctly\n997: - Status queries return correct information\n998: - Error handling is comprehensive with clear messages\n999: - Verbose mode provides detailed logging\n1000: - Code passes static analysis (flake8, mypy, black)\n1001: - Documentation is complete and accurate\n1002: - Examples work correctly\n1003: \n1004: ### Dependencies\n1005: - Python 3.10+\n1006: - typer[all] >=0.9.0\n1007: - pydantic >=2.0.0\n1008: - pyyaml >=6.0\n1009: - httpx >=0.24.0\n1010: - kubernetes >=28.0.0\n1011: - rich >=13.0.0\n1012: - pytest (for testing)\n1013: - flake8 (for linting)\n1014: - mypy (for type checking)\n1015: - black (for formatting)\n1016: - Kubernetes cluster (for testing)\n1017: - HTTP server (for invoke testing)\n1018: \n1019: ### Blocked By\n1020: - None (design stage ST-3 completed)\n1021: \n1022: ### Blocks\n1023: - None\n1024: \n1025: ### Notes\n1026: - Invoke and status commands depend on publish command\n1027: - Supports both AgentCube and Kubernetes providers\n1028: - Uses async HTTP client for invoke requests\n1029: - Comprehensive error handling and logging\n1030: - Rich progress display for better UX\n1031: - Extensive test coverage ensures reliability\n1032: - Session management for agentcube provider\n1033: - Metadata persistence for deployment tracking\n1034: - Status checking for both CR and standard deployments\n\n(End of file - total 1034 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-023 — CLI invoke/status 命令 Implementation Tasks\n\n**Module**: `cmd/cli`\n**Language**: Python\n**Size**: M\n**Design Stage**: ST-3 Completed\n\n## Task Breakdown\n\n### Task 1: Verify invoke command interface in main.py\n- [ ] Verify invoke command exists in agentcube/cli/main.py\n- [ ] Verify all required parameters are defined:\n  - [ ] workspace (default \".\", short flag \"-f\")\n  - [ ] payload (default \"{}\")\n  - [ ] header_list (optional, can be specified multiple times)\n  - [ ] provider (default \"agentcube\")\n  - [ ] verbose (default False)\n- [ ] Verify parameter types match design (str, Optional[str], List[str], bool)\n- [ ] Verify help text is present for all parameters\n- [ ] Verify command docstring describes functionality","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-023/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775871111679,"end":1775871111724}}}}
