{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775871125602,"sessionID":"ses_285d570caffeupuoMbNOk82vM3","part":{"id":"prt_d7a2ae20e0017hjoIwffb1qXG4","messageID":"msg_d7a2ad606001naI1skHUV4yTIn","sessionID":"ses_285d570caffeupuoMbNOk82vM3","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-bdfb60555a6749c6a7e700a66e444e28","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-024/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-024/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-024 — DockerService 封装 (DockerService Encapsulation)\n2: \n3: ## 模块信息\n4: \n5: - **模块**: `cmd/cli`\n6: - **语言**: Python\n7: - **规模**: M\n8: - **关联需求**: AR-024\n9: \n10: ## 架构概述\n11: \n12: ### 设计目标\n13: \n14: DockerService 是一个封装了 Docker SDK 操作的服务类，为 AgentCube CLI 的构建和发布工作流提供统一的 Docker 接口。该服务封装了 Docker SDK 的复杂性，提供了简洁的高级 API 用于镜像构建、推送、标记和管理等操作，同时提供完善的错误处理、日志记录和输入验证机制。\n15: \n16: ### 核心组件\n17: \n18: ```\n19: agentcube/services/\n20: ├── docker_service.py         # DockerService 主要实现\n21: ├── __init__.py               # 服务包导出\n22: └── [exceptions.py]           # 自定义异常类（可选）\n23: ```\n24: \n25: ### 架构原则\n26: \n27: 1. **封装复杂性**: 将 Docker SDK 的复杂性封装在服务层，提供简洁的高级 API\n28: 2. **延迟初始化**: Docker 客户端采用延迟初始化（Lazy Initialization）模式\n29: 3. **错误隔离**: 将 Docker SDK 异常包装为服务特定异常，避免直接暴露底层实现\n30: 4. **安全第一**: 妥善处理敏感信息（如密码），不记录到日志中\n31: 5. **可观测性**: 提供可选的详细日志模式，支持调试和故障排查\n32: 6. **幂等性**: 所有操作设计为幂等的，可以安全地重复执行\n33: \n34: ## 组件设计\n35: \n36: ### DockerService 类\n37: \n38: #### 数据结构\n39: \n40: ```python\n41: import logging\n42: import time\n43: from pathlib import Path\n44: from typing import Any, Dict, Optional\n45: \n46: import docker\n47: from docker.errors import DockerException\n48: \n49: \n50: logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n51: \n52: \n53: class DockerService:\n54:     \"\"\"Service for Docker operations.\"\"\"\n55: \n56:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None:\n57:         \"\"\"Initialize the Docker service.\n58: \n59:         Args:\n60:             verbose: Enable verbose logging for debugging.\n61: \n62:         Raises:\n63:             RuntimeError: If Docker client initialization fails.\n64:         \"\"\"\n65:         self.verbose = verbose\n66:         if verbose:\n67:             logging.basicConfig(level=logging.DEBUG)\n68:         self._client: Optional[docker.DockerClient] = None\n69: \n70:     @property\n71:     def client(self) -> docker.DockerClient:\n72:         \"\"\"Get or create Docker client using lazy initialization.\n73: \n74:         Returns:\n75:             The Docker client instance.\n76: \n77:         Raises:\n78:             DockerException: If Docker daemon is not available.\n79:         \"\"\"\n80:         if self._client is None:\n81:             self._client = docker.from_env()\n82:         return self._client\n83: ```\n84: \n85: #### 公共 API 方法\n86: \n87: ##### 1. Docker 可用性检查\n88: \n89: ```python\n90: def check_docker_available(self) -> bool:\n91:     \"\"\"Check if Docker daemon is available and running.\n92: \n93:     Returns:\n94:         True if Docker is available, False otherwise.\n95: \n96:     Note:\n97:         This method does not raise exceptions on failure, making it\n98:         suitable for availability checks before operations.\n99:     \"\"\"\n100:     try:\n101:         self.client.ping()\n102:         return True\n103:     except DockerException as e:\n104:         logger.warning(f\"Docker not available: {e}\")\n105:         return False\n106: ```\n107: \n108: ##### 2. 镜像构建\n109: \n110: ```python\n111: def build_image(\n112:     self,\n113:     dockerfile_path: Path,\n114:     context_path: Path,\n115:     image_name: str,\n116:     tag: str = \"latest\",\n117:     build_args: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n118: ) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n119:     \"\"\"Build a Docker image from a Dockerfile.\n120: \n121:     Args:\n122:         dockerfile_path: Path to the Dockerfile.\n123:         context_path: Path to the build context directory.\n124:         image_name: Name for the resulting image.\n125:         tag: Tag for the image (default: \"latest\").\n126:         build_args: Optional build arguments for proxy configuration.\n127: \n128:     Returns:\n129:         Dict containing:\n130:             - image_name: Full image name with tag.\n131:             - image_id: SHA256 hash of the image.\n132:             - image_size: Human-readable size string.\n133:             - size_bytes: Size in bytes.\n134:             - build_time: Timestamp of the build.\n135: \n136:     Raises:\n137:         FileNotFoundError: If dockerfile_path or context_path does not exist.\n138:         ValueError: If image_name or dockerfile_path is invalid.\n139:         RuntimeError: If Docker is not available or build fails.\n140:     \"\"\"\n141:     if not self.check_docker_available():\n142:         raise RuntimeError(\"Docker is not available or not running\")\n143: \n144:     logger.info(f\"Building image {image_name}:{tag} from {dockerfile_path}\")\n145:     full_image_name = f\"{image_name}:{tag}\"\n146: \n147:     try:\n148:         image, build_logs = self.client.images.build(\n149:             path=str(context_path),\n150:             dockerfile=str(dockerfile_path),\n151:             tag=full_image_name,\n152:             buildargs=build_args,\n153:             rm=True,\n154:             forcerm=True,\n155:         )\n156: \n157:         image_info = self.get_image_info(full_image_name)\n158:         image_info[\"build_time\"] = time.time()\n159: \n160:         return image_info\n161: \n162:     except DockerException as e:\n163:         raise RuntimeError(f\"Failed to build Docker image: {e}\") from e\n164: ```\n165: \n166: ##### 3. 镜像信息查询\n167: \n168: ```python\n169: def get_image_info(self, image_name: str) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n170:     \"\"\"Get detailed information about a Docker image.\n171: \n172:     Args:\n173:         image_name: Name of the image (with or without tag).\n174: \n175:     Returns:\n176:         Dict containing:\n177:             - image_name: The image name.\n178:             - image_id: SHA256 hash (first 12 characters).\n179:             - image_size: Human-readable size string.\n180:             - size_bytes: Size in bytes.\n181: \n182:     Note:\n183:         Returns empty dict if image is not found.\n184:     \"\"\"\n185:     try:\n186:         image = self.client.images.get(image_name)\n187:         attrs = image.attrs\n188: \n189:         image_id = attrs[\"Id\"].split(\":\")[-1][:12]\n190:         size_bytes = attrs.get(\"Size\", 0)\n191: \n192:         return {\n193:             \"image_name\": image_name,\n194:             \"image_id\": image_id,\n195:             \"image_size\": self._format_size(size_bytes),\n196:             \"size_bytes\": size_bytes,\n197:         }\n198: \n199:     except DockerException as e:\n200:         logger.warning(f\"Failed to get image info for {image_name}: {e}\")\n201:         return {}\n202: ```\n203: \n204: ##### 4. 镜像推送\n205: \n206: ```python\n207: def push_image(\n208:     self,\n209:     image_name: str,\n210:     registry_url: Optional[str] = None,\n211:     username: Optional[str] = None,\n212:     password: Optional[str] = None,\n213: ) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n214:     \"\"\"Push a Docker image to a container registry.\n215: \n216:     Args:\n217:         image_name: Local image name to push.\n218:         registry_url: Optional registry URL (e.g., \"registry.example.com/username\").\n219:         username: Optional username for private registry authentication.\n220:         password: Optional password for private registry authentication.\n221: \n222:     Returns:\n223:         Dict containing:\n224:             - pushed_image: Full name of the pushed image.\n225:             - push_time: Timestamp of the push operation.\n226: \n227:     Raises:\n228:         RuntimeError: If Docker is not available, authentication fails,\n229:                      or push operation fails.\n230:         ValueError: If image does not exist locally.\n231: \n232:     Security Note:\n233:         Passwords are never logged or stored in instance variables.\n234:     \"\"\"\n235:     if not self.check_docker_available():\n236:         raise RuntimeError(\"Docker is not available or not running\")\n237: \n238:     target_image = image_name\n239:     if registry_url:\n240:         target_image = f\"{registry_url}/{image_name}\"\n241:         self._tag_image_sdk(image_name, target_image)\n242: \n243:     if username and password:\n244:         self._docker_login_sdk(registry_url, username, password)\n245: \n246:     logger.info(f\"Pushing image {target_image}\")\n247: \n248:     try:\n249:         push_logs = self.client.images.push(target_image, stream=True, decode=True)\n250: \n251:         for line in push_logs:\n252:             if \"error\" in line:\n253:                 raise RuntimeError(f\"Failed to push image: {line['error']}\")\n254:             if self.verbose:\n255:                 logger.debug(f\"Push log: {line}\")\n256: \n257:         return {\n258:             \"pushed_image\": target_image,\n259:             \"push_time\": str(time.time()),\n260:         }\n261: \n262:     except DockerException as e:\n263:         raise RuntimeError(f\"Failed to push Docker image: {e}\") from e\n264: ```\n265: \n266: ##### 5. 镜像删除\n267: \n268: ```python\n269: def remove_image(self, image_name: str, force: bool = True) -> bool:\n270:     \"\"\"Remove a Docker image from the local daemon.\n271: \n272:     Args:\n273:         image_name: Name of the image to remove.\n274:         force: Force removal even if image is in use (default: True).\n275: \n276:     Returns:\n277:         True if removal succeeded, False otherwise.\n278: \n279:     Note:\n280:         This method does not raise exceptions for non-existent images,\n281:         making it safe for cleanup operations.\n282:     \"\"\"\n283:     try:\n284:         self.client.images.remove(image_name, force=force)\n285:         logger.info(f\"Removed image {image_name}\")\n286:         return True\n287:     except DockerException as e:\n288:         logger.warning(f\"Failed to remove image {image_name}: {e}\")\n289:         return False\n290: ```\n291: \n292: #### 私有辅助方法\n293: \n294: ##### 1. Docker registry 登录\n295: \n296: ```python\n297: def _docker_login_sdk(self, registry: Optional[str], username: str, password: str) -> None:\n298:     \"\"\"Log in to a Docker registry.\n299: \n300:     Args:\n301:         registry: Registry URL or None for Docker Hub.\n302:         username: Username for authentication.\n303:         password: Password for authentication.\n304: \n305:     Raises:\n306:         RuntimeError: If authentication fails.\n307: \n308:     Security Note:\n309:         Password is never logged. Authentication is handled\n310:         securely through Docker SDK.\n311:     \"\"\"\n312:     try:\n313:         self.client.login(username=username, password=password, registry=registry)\n314:         logger.info(f\"Successfully logged in to registry: {registry or 'default'}\")\n315:     except DockerException as e:\n316:         raise RuntimeError(f\"Failed to log in to Docker registry: {e}\") from e\n317: ```\n318: \n319: ##### 2. 镜像标记\n320: \n321: ```python\n322: def _tag_image_sdk(self, source_image: str, target_image: str) -> None:\n323:     \"\"\"Tag a Docker image with a new name.\n324: \n325:     Args:\n326:         source_image: Existing image name.\n327:         target_image: New image name/tag.\n328: \n329:     Raises:\n330:         RuntimeError: If tagging fails.\n331:     \"\"\"\n332:     try:\n333:         image = self.client.images.get(source_image)\n334:         image.tag(target_image, force=True)\n335:         logger.info(f\"Tagged {source_image} as {target_image}\")\n336:     except DockerException as e:\n337:         raise RuntimeError(f\"Failed to tag Docker image: {e}\") from e\n338: ```\n339: \n340: ##### 3. 大小格式化\n341: \n342: ```python\n343: def _format_size(self, size_bytes: int) -> str:\n344:     \"\"\"Format byte size into human-readable format.\n345: \n346:     Args:\n347:         size_bytes: Size in bytes.\n348: \n349:     Returns:\n350:         Human-readable size string (e.g., \"2.00 GB\").\n351: \n352:     Example:\n353:         >>> self._format_size(2147483648)\n354:         \"2.00 GB\"\n355:     \"\"\"\n356:     size = float(size_bytes)\n357:     for unit in [\"B\", \"KB\", \"MB\", \"GB\"]:\n358:         if size < 1024:\n359:             return f\"{size:.2f} {unit}\"\n360:         size /= 1024\n361:     return f\"{size:.2f} TB\"\n362: ```\n363: \n364: ## 数据流\n365: \n366: ### 镜像构建流程\n367: \n368: ```\n369: ┌─────────────────┐\n370: │ BuildRuntime    │\n371: │ (调用方)        │\n372: └────────┬────────┘\n373:          │\n374:          ▼\n375: ┌─────────────────┐\n376: │ build_image()   │\n377: │ DockerService   │\n378: └────────┬────────┘\n379:          │\n380:          ├─────────────────────────────────┐\n381:          │                                 │\n382:          ▼                                 ▼\n383: ┌─────────────────┐              ┌─────────────────┐\n384: │ check_docker_   │              │ validate_paths()│\n385: │ available()     │              │                 │\n386: └────────┬────────┘              └────────┬────────┘\n387:          │                                 │\n388:          ▼                                 ▼\n389:      ┌────┴────┐                    ┌──────┴──────┐\n390:      │         │                    │             │\n391:      ▼         ▼                    ▼             ▼\n392:  ┌──────┐  ┌──────┐           ┌──────────┐  ┌──────────┐\n393:  │可用? │  │不可用?│          │路径有效? │  │路径无效? │\n394:  └───┬──┘  └───┬──┘           └────┬─────┘  └────┬─────┘\n395:      │          │                    │             │\n396:      ▼          ▼                    ▼             ▼\n397:  ┌──────┐  ┌──────┐            ┌──────────┐  ┌──────────┐\n398:  │继续  │  │抛出   │            │调用      │  │抛出      │\n399:  │构建  │  │Runtime│            │Docker    │  │FileNotFound│\n400:  └───┬──┘  └──────┘            │SDK.build │  └──────────┘\n401:      │                       └────┬─────┘\n402:      │                            │\n403:      ▼                            ▼\n404: ┌─────────────────┐      ┌─────────────────┐\n405: │ get_image_info()│      │ 流式输出日志    │\n406: │                 │      │ (verbose模式)   │\n407: └────────┬────────┘      └─────────────────┘\n408:          │\n409:          ▼\n410: ┌─────────────────┐\n411: │ 返回结果dict    │\n412: │ (image_id,      │\n413: │  size, time)    │\n414: └─────────────────┘\n415: ```\n416: \n417: ### 镜像推送流程\n418: \n419: ```\n420: ┌─────────────────┐\n421: │ PublishRuntime  │\n422: │ (调用方)        │\n423: └────────┬────────┘\n424:          │\n425:          ▼\n426: ┌─────────────────┐\n427: │ push_image()    │\n428: │ DockerService   │\n429: └────────┬────────┘\n430:          │\n431:          ├─────────────────────────────────┐\n432:          │                                 │\n433:          ▼                                 ▼\n434: ┌─────────────────┐              ┌─────────────────┐\n435: │ check_docker_   │              │ validate_image()│\n436: │ available()     │              │                 │\n437: └────────┬────────┘              └────────┬────────┘\n438:          │                                 │\n439:          ▼                                 ▼\n440:      ┌────┴────┐                    ┌──────┴──────┐\n441:      │         │                    │             │\n442:      ▼         ▼                    ▼             ▼\n443:  ┌──────┐  ┌──────┐           ┌──────────┐  ┌──────────┐\n444:  │可用? │  │不可用?│          │镜像存在? │  │镜像不存在?│\n445:  └───┬──┘  └───┬──┘           └────┬─────┘  └────┬─────┘\n446:      │          │                    │             │\n447:      ▼          ▼                    ▼             ▼\n448:  ┌──────┐  ┌──────┐            ┌──────────┐  ┌──────────┐\n449:  │检查  │  │抛出   │            │检查      │  │抛出      │\n450:  │registry│ │Runtime│            │是否需要  │  │ValueError│\n451:  │URL?   │  │Error  │            │重新标记  │  │          │\n452:  └───┬──┘  └──────┘            └────┬─────┘  └──────────┘\n453:      │                            │\n454:      ▼                            ▼\n455: ┌──────────┐              ┌───────────────┐\n456: │需要登录? │              │ _tag_image_sdk│\n457: └────┬─────┘              └───────┬───────┘\n458:      │                            │\n459:   ┌──┴──┐                         ▼\n460:   │     │                    ┌──────────────┐\n461:   ▼     ▼                    │需要认证?     │\n462: ┌────┐ ┌────┐                └────┬─────────┘\n463: │是  │ │否  │                     │\n464: └┬───┘ └┬──┘                  ┌────┴────┐\n465:  │     │                      │         │\n466:  ▼     ▼                      ▼         ▼\n467: ┌─────────┐              ┌─────────┐ ┌─────────┐\n468: │_docker_ │              │是       │ │否       │\n469: │login_sdk│              └────┬────┘ └────┬────┘\n470: └────┬────┘                   │           │\n471:      │                       ▼           ▼\n472:      ▼                  ┌─────────┐  ┌─────────┐\n473: ┌─────────┐             │_docker_ │  │调用     │\n474: │调用     │             │login_sdk│  │Docker   │\n475: │Docker   │             └────┬────┘  │SDK.push │\n476: │SDK.push │                  │       └────┬────┘\n477: └────┬────┘                  ▼            │\n478:      │                 ┌─────────┐        │\n479:      ▼                 │调用     │        │\n480: ┌─────────┐            │Docker   │        ▼\n481: │流式输出 │            │SDK.push │  ┌─────────────┐\n482: │日志     │            └────┬────┘  │验证推送结果 │\n483: │(verbose)│                 │       └──────┬──────┘\n484: └─────────┘                 ▼              │\n485:                    ┌─────────────┐          │\n486:                    │流式输出日志  │          │\n487:                    │(verbose)     │          ▼\n488:                    └─────────────┘  ┌─────────────┐\n489:                                     │返回结果dict │\n490:                                     └─────────────┘\n491: ```\n492: \n493: ## 序列图\n494: \n495: ### 成功构建镜像\n496: \n497: ```\n498: BuildRuntime    DockerService    Docker Client    Docker Daemon\n499:      │                 │                 │                  │\n500:      │ build_image()   │                 │                  │\n501:      │────────────────►│                 │                  │\n502:      │                 │ check_docker_   │                  │\n503:      │                 │ available()     │                  │\n504:      │                 │────────────────►│                  │\n505:      │                 │                 │ ping()           │\n506:      │                 │                 │─────────────────►│\n507:      │                 │                 │◄─────────────────│\n508:      │                 │◄────────────────│                  │\n509:      │                 │ images.build()  │                  │\n510:      │                 │────────────────►│                  │\n511:      │                 │                 │ build context    │\n512:      │                 │                 │─────────────────►│\n513:      │                 │                 │◄─────────────────│\n514:      │                 │                 │ (stream logs)    │\n515:      │                 │◄────────────────│                  │\n516:      │                 │ get_image_info()│                  │\n517:      │                 │────────────────►│                  │\n518:      │                 │                 │ images.get()     │\n519:      │                 │                 │─────────────────►│\n520:      │                 │                 │◄─────────────────│\n521:      │                 │◄────────────────│                  │\n522:      │◄────────────────│                 │                  │\n523:      │  result dict    │                 │                  │\n524: ```\n525: \n526: ### 推送镜像到私有仓库\n527: \n528: ```\n529: PublishRuntime  DockerService    Docker Client    Docker Daemon   Registry\n530:       │                │                 │                  │           │\n531:       │ push_image()   │                 │                  │           │\n532:       │───────────────►│                 │                  │           │\n533:       │                │ check_docker_   │                  │           │\n534:       │                │ available()     │                  │           │\n535:       │                │────────────────►│                  │           │\n536:       │                │                 │ ping()           │           │\n537:       │                │                 │─────────────────►│           │\n538:       │                │                 │◄─────────────────│           │\n539:       │                │◄────────────────│                  │           │\n540:       │                │ _tag_image_sdk()│                  │           │\n541:       │                │────────────────►│                  │           │\n542:       │                │                 │ image.tag()      │           │\n543:       │                │                 │─────────────────►│           │\n544:       │                │                 │◄─────────────────│           │\n545:       │                │◄────────────────│                  │           │\n546:       │                │ _docker_login_  │                  │           │\n547:       │                │ sdk()           │                  │           │\n548:       │                │────────────────►│                  │           │\n549:       │                │                 │ login()          │           │\n550:       │                │                 │─────────────────────────────►│\n551:       │                │                 │◄─────────────────────────────│\n552:       │                │◄────────────────│                  │           │\n553:       │                │ images.push()   │                  │           │\n554:       │                │────────────────►│                  │           │\n555:       │                │                 │ push layers      │           │\n556:       │                │                 │─────────────────────────────►│\n557:       │                │                 │◄─────────────────────────────│\n558:       │                │                 │ (stream logs)    │           │\n559:       │                │◄────────────────│                  │           │\n560:       │◄───────────────│                 │                  │           │\n561:       │  result dict   │                 │                  │           │\n562: ```\n563: \n564: ## 错误处理\n565: \n566: ### 错误分类\n567: \n568: | 错误类型 | 异常类 | 触发场景 | 处理策略 |\n569: |---------|--------|---------|---------|\n570: | Docker 不可用 | `RuntimeError` | `check_docker_available()` 返回 `False` | 操作前检查，提供清晰错误信息 |\n571: | 文件不存在 | `FileNotFoundError` | dockerfile_path 或 context_path 不存在 | 验证输入路径，提供路径信息 |\n572: | 镜像不存在 | `ValueError` | 尝试操作不存在的镜像 | 验证镜像存在性 |\n573: | 构建失败 | `RuntimeError` | Docker 构建过程失败 | 包装 Docker SDK 异常 |\n574: | 认证失败 | `RuntimeError` | Registry 认证失败 | 不记录密码，提供通用错误信息 |\n575: | 网络错误 | `RuntimeError` | Registry 不可达 | 提供网络相关信息 |\n576: | 标记失败 | `RuntimeError` | 镜像标记失败 | 提供源/目标镜像名称 |\n577: \n578: ### 异常处理策略\n579: \n580: ```python\n581: def _handle_docker_exception(self, operation: str, exception: DockerException) -> None:\n582:     \"\"\"Handle Docker SDK exceptions with context.\n583: \n584:     Args:\n585:         operation: Name of the operation being performed.\n586:         exception: The Docker SDK exception.\n587: \n588:     Raises:\n589:         RuntimeError: Wrapped exception with additional context.\n590:     \"\"\"\n591:     error_msg = f\"Docker {operation} failed: {str(exception)}\"\n592:     logger.error(error_msg)\n593:     raise RuntimeError(error_msg) from exception\n594: ```\n595: \n596: ### 错误恢复机制\n597: \n598: 1. **客户端重连**: 如果 Docker 守护进程重启，客户端属性会重新初始化\n599: 2. **幂等操作**: 所有操作设计为可安全重试\n600: 3. **非关键失败**: `remove_image()` 等操作失败不抛出异常，仅返回 `False`\n601: \n602: ## 安全考虑\n603: \n604: ### 凭证处理\n605: \n606: ```python\n607: def _docker_login_sdk(self, registry: Optional[str], username: str, password: str) -> None:\n608:     \"\"\"Secure login to Docker registry.\n609: \n610:     Security Measures:\n611:         1. Password is never logged or stored in instance variables.\n612:         2. Uses Docker SDK's secure authentication mechanism.\n613:         3. Password is only held in memory during the login call.\n614:         4. Log messages use placeholders for sensitive data.\n615:     \"\"\"\n616:     try:\n617:         # Password is only passed to Docker SDK, never logged\n618:         self.client.login(username=username, password=password, registry=registry)\n619: \n620:         # Log success without revealing credentials\n621:         registry_name = registry or \"Docker Hub\"\n622:         logger.info(f\"Successfully logged in to registry: {registry_name}\")\n623:     except DockerException as e:\n624:         # Error message does not include password\n625:         raise RuntimeError(\n626:             f\"Failed to log in to Docker registry '{registry or 'Docker Hub'}': {e}\"\n627:         ) from e\n628: ```\n629: \n630: ### 路径验证\n631: \n632: ```python\n633: def _validate_build_paths(self, dockerfile_path: Path, context_path: Path) -> None:\n634:     \"\"\"Validate file paths before Docker operations.\n635: \n636:     Security Measures:\n637:         1. Resolves absolute paths to prevent directory traversal.\n638:         2. Validates paths exist before operations.\n639:         3. Validates context_path is a directory.\n640:         4. Validates dockerfile_path is a file.\n641: \n642:     Raises:\n643:         FileNotFoundError: If paths do not exist.\n644:         ValueError: If paths have invalid types.\n645:     \"\"\"\n646:     dockerfile_path = dockerfile_path.resolve()\n647:     context_path = context_path.resolve()\n648: \n649:     if not dockerfile_path.exists():\n650:         raise FileNotFoundError(f\"Dockerfile not found: {dockerfile_path}\")\n651:     if not dockerfile_path.is_file():\n652:         raise ValueError(f\"Dockerfile path is not a file: {dockerfile_path}\")\n653: \n654:     if not context_path.exists():\n655:         raise FileNotFoundError(f\"Build context not found: {context_path}\")\n656:     if not context_path.is_dir():\n657:         raise ValueError(f\"Build context path is not a directory: {context_path}\")\n658: ```\n659: \n660: ### 日志安全\n661: \n662: ```python\n663: # Good: No sensitive information\n664: logger.info(f\"Pushing image {target_image}\")\n665: logger.info(f\"Successfully logged in to registry: {registry_name}\")\n666: \n667: # Bad: Never log passwords\n668: # logger.info(f\"Logging in with password: {password}\")  # DON'T DO THIS\n669: ```\n670: \n671: ## API 契约\n672: \n673: ### 公共 API 摘要\n674: \n675: | 方法 | 输入参数 | 返回值 | 可能抛出 |\n676: |------|---------|--------|---------|\n677: | `__init__` | `verbose: bool = False` | `DockerService` 实例 | `RuntimeError` |\n678: | `check_docker_available` | - | `bool` | - |\n679: | `build_image` | `dockerfile_path`, `context_path`, `image_name`, `tag`, `build_args` | `Dict[str, Any]` | `RuntimeError`, `FileNotFoundError`, `ValueError` |\n680: | `get_image_info` | `image_name` | `Dict[str, Any]` | - |\n681: | `push_image` | `image_name`, `registry_url`, `username`, `password` | `Dict[str, Any]` | `RuntimeError`, `ValueError` |\n682: | `remove_image` | `image_name`, `force` | `bool` | - |\n683: \n684: ### 返回值结构\n685: \n686: #### build_image() 返回值\n687: \n688: ```python\n689: {\n690:     \"image_name\": \"myagent:latest\",\n691:     \"image_id\": \"abc123def456\",\n692:     \"image_size\": \"2.00 GB\",\n693:     \"size_bytes\": 2147483648,\n694:     \"build_time\": 1712851200.123456\n695: }\n696: ```\n697: \n698: #### push_image() 返回值\n699: \n700: ```python\n701: {\n702:     \"pushed_image\": \"registry.example.com/username/myagent:latest\",\n703:     \"push_time\": \"1712851200.123456\"\n704: }\n705: ```\n706: \n707: #### get_image_info() 返回值\n708: \n709: ```python\n710: {\n711:     \"image_name\": \"myagent:latest\",\n712:     \"image_id\": \"abc123def456\",\n713:     \"image_size\": \"2.00 GB\",\n714:     \"size_bytes\": 2147483648\n715: }\n716: ```\n717: \n718: ## 依赖项\n719: \n720: | 依赖 | 版本 | 用途 |\n721: |------|------|------|\n722: | `docker` | `>=6.0.0` | Docker SDK for Python |\n723: | `pathlib` | - | 文件路径处理（标准库） |\n724: | `logging` | - | 日志记录（标准库） |\n725: | `typing` | - | 类型注解（标准库） |\n726: | `time` | - | 时间戳（标准库） |\n727: \n728: ### Docker SDK 依赖\n729: \n730: DockerService 依赖 `docker.from_env()` 初始化客户端，该函数会自动：\n731: \n732: 1. 从环境变量 `DOCKER_HOST` 读取 Docker daemon 地址\n733: 2. 使用默认的 Unix socket 或 Windows named pipe\n734: 3. 支持环境变量配置：\n735:    - `DOCKER_HOST`: Docker daemon 地址\n736:    - `DOCKER_TLS_VERIFY`: TLS 验证\n737:    - `DOCKER_CERT_PATH`: 证书路径\n738: \n739: ## 测试策略\n740: \n741: ### 单元测试\n742: \n743: #### 测试覆盖率目标\n744: \n745: - **行覆盖率**: ≥ 90%\n746: - **分支覆盖率**: ≥ 85%\n747: \n748: #### 测试用例分类\n749: \n750: **1. 初始化测试**\n751: \n752: ```python\n753: def test_docker_service_init_verbose():\n754:     \"\"\"Test DockerService initialization with verbose=True.\"\"\"\n755:     service = DockerService(verbose=True)\n756:     assert service.verbose is True\n757:     assert service._client is None  # Lazy initialization\n758: \n759: def test_docker_service_init_non_verbose():\n760:     \"\"\"Test DockerService initialization with verbose=False.\"\"\"\n761:     service = DockerService(verbose=False)\n762:     assert service.verbose is False\n763: ```\n764: \n765: **2. 可用性检查测试**\n766: \n767: ```python\n768: def test_check_docker_available_success():\n769:     \"\"\"Test successful Docker availability check.\"\"\"\n770:     with mock.patch('docker.from_env') as mock_docker:\n771:         mock_client = mock.Mock()\n772:         mock_docker.return_value = mock_client\n773:         mock_client.ping.return_value = True\n774: \n775:         service = DockerService()\n776:         assert service.check_docker_available() is True\n777: \n778: def test_check_docker_available_failure():\n779:     \"\"\"Test failed Docker availability check.\"\"\"\n780:     with mock.patch('docker.from_env') as mock_docker:\n781:         mock_client = mock.Mock()\n782:         mock_docker.return_value = mock_client\n783:         mock_client.ping.side_effect = DockerException(\"Connection failed\")\n784: \n785:         service = DockerService()\n786:         assert service.check_docker_available() is False\n787: ```\n788: \n789: **3. 镜像构建测试**\n790: \n791: ```python\n792: def test_build_image_success():\n793:     \"\"\"Test successful image build.\"\"\"\n794:     with mock.patch('docker.from_env') as mock_docker:\n795:         mock_client = mock.Mock()\n796:         mock_docker.return_value = mock_client\n797: \n798:         mock_image = mock.Mock()\n799:         mock_image.attrs = {\n800:             'Id': 'sha256:abcdef123456',\n801:             'Size': 1024 * 1024  # 1 MB\n802:         }\n803:         mock_client.images.build.return_value = (mock_image, [])\n804: \n805:         service = DockerService()\n806:         result = service.build_image(\n807:             dockerfile_path=Path(\"Dockerfile\"),\n808:             context_path=Path(\".\"),\n809:             image_name=\"test-image\"\n810:         )\n811: \n812:         assert result['image_name'] == \"test-image:latest\"\n813:         assert result['image_id'] == \"abcdef123456\"\n814:         assert \"build_time\" in result\n815: \n816: def test_build_image_docker_unavailable():\n817:     \"\"\"Test build failure when Docker is unavailable.\"\"\"\n818:     with mock.patch('docker.from_env') as mock_docker:\n819:         mock_client = mock.Mock()\n820:         mock_docker.return_value = mock_client\n821:         mock_client.ping.side_effect = DockerException(\"Not available\")\n822: \n823:         service = DockerService()\n824: \n825:         with pytest.raises(RuntimeError, match=\"Docker is not available\"):\n826:             service.build_image(\n827:                 dockerfile_path=Path(\"Dockerfile\"),\n828:                 context_path=Path(\".\"),\n829:                 image_name=\"test-image\"\n830:             )\n831: ```\n832: \n833: **4. 镜像推送测试**\n834: \n835: ```python\n836: def test_push_image_with_authentication():\n837:     \"\"\"Test pushing image with registry authentication.\"\"\"\n838:     with mock.patch('docker.from_env') as mock_docker:\n839:         mock_client = mock.Mock()\n840:         mock_docker.return_value = mock_client\n841: \n842:         mock_client.images.push.return_value = [{'status': 'success'}]\n843: \n844:         service = DockerService()\n845:         result = service.push_image(\n846:             image_name=\"test-image\",\n847:             registry_url=\"registry.example.com/user\",\n848:             username=\"testuser\",\n849:             password=\"testpass\"\n850:         )\n851: \n852:         # Verify login was called\n853:         mock_client.login.assert_called_once_with(\n854:             username=\"testuser\",\n855:             password=\"testpass\",\n856:             registry=\"registry.example.com/user\"\n857:         )\n858: \n859:         # Verify push was called with correct image name\n860:         mock_client.images.push.assert_called_once_with(\n861:             \"registry.example.com/user/test-image\",\n862:             stream=True,\n863:             decode=True\n864:         )\n865: \n866:         assert result['pushed_image'] == \"registry.example.com/user/test-image\"\n867: \n868: def test_push_image_password_not_logged():\n869:     \"\"\"Test that password is never logged during push.\"\"\"\n870:     with mock.patch('docker.from_env') as mock_docker:\n871:         mock_client = mock.Mock()\n872:         mock_docker.return_value = mock_client\n873: \n874:         mock_client.images.push.return_value = [{'status': 'success'}]\n875: \n876:         service = DockerService(verbose=True)\n877:         result = service.push_image(\n878:             image_name=\"test-image\",\n879:             username=\"testuser\",\n880:             password=\"secret123\"\n881:         )\n882: \n883:         # Verify password was passed to login but never logged\n884:         mock_client.login.assert_called_once()\n885:         assert \"secret123\" not in str(mock_client.login.call_args)\n886: ```\n887: \n888: ### 集成测试\n889: \n890: #### 测试环境要求\n891: \n892: - Docker daemon 运行中\n893: - 测试镜像仓库（可选，用于推送测试）\n894: - 测试 Dockerfile\n895: \n896: #### 集成测试用例\n897: \n898: ```python\n899: def test_build_and_push_integration():\n900:     \"\"\"End-to-end test: build and push image.\"\"\"\n901:     service = DockerService(verbose=True)\n902: \n903:     # Build image\n904:     build_result = service.build_image(\n905:         dockerfile_path=Path(\"test/Dockerfile\"),\n906:         context_path=Path(\"test\"),\n907:         image_name=\"integration-test\"\n908:     )\n909: \n910:     assert build_result['image_name'] == \"integration-test:latest\"\n911: \n912:     # Verify image exists\n913:     image_info = service.get_image_info(\"integration-test:latest\")\n914:     assert image_info['image_name'] == \"integration-test:latest\"\n915: \n916:     # Clean up\n917:     assert service.remove_image(\"integration-test:latest\") is True\n918: ```\n919: \n920: ### Mock 测试策略\n921: \n922: 使用 `unittest.mock` 模拟 Docker SDK：\n923: \n924: ```python\n925: @pytest.fixture\n926: def mock_docker_service():\n927:     \"\"\"Fixture providing a mocked DockerService.\"\"\"\n928:     with mock.patch('docker.from_env') as mock_docker:\n929:         mock_client = mock.Mock()\n930:         mock_docker.return_value = mock_client\n931:         mock_client.ping.return_value = True\n932:         service = DockerService()\n933:         yield service, mock_client\n934: ```\n935: \n936: ## 性能考虑\n937: \n938: ### 内存使用\n939: \n940: 1. **流式处理**: 构建和推送操作使用流式日志，避免将所有输出加载到内存\n941: 2. **延迟初始化**: Docker 客户端只在需要时初始化\n942: 3. **无状态设计**: 方法调用间不保持状态，减少内存占用\n943: \n944: ### 并发处理\n945: \n946: ```python\n947: # DockerService 是线程安全的（只读操作）\n948: # 但不建议并发执行构建或推送操作\n949: # 因为 Docker SDK 本身不是完全线程安全的\n950: \n951: # 推荐：为每个操作创建新的 DockerService 实例\n952: service1 = DockerService()\n953: service2 = DockerService()\n954: \n955: # 或者使用队列串行化操作\n956: from queue import Queue\n957: from threading import Thread\n958: \n959: def build_worker(queue: Queue):\n960:     while True:\n961:         task = queue.get()\n962:         service = DockerService()\n963:         service.build_image(**task)\n964:         queue.task_done()\n965: ```\n966: \n967: ### 超时配置\n968: \n969: 考虑为长时间操作添加超时（未来增强）：\n970: \n971: ```python\n972: def build_image(\n973:     self,\n974:     dockerfile_path: Path,\n975:     context_path: Path,\n976:     image_name: str,\n977:     tag: str = \"latest\",\n978:     build_args: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n979:     timeout: Optional[int] = None,  # 新增：超时配置\n980: ) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n981:     \"\"\"Build a Docker image with optional timeout.\"\"\"\n982:     # TODO: 实现超时逻辑\n983:     pass\n984: ```\n985: \n986: ## 使用示例\n987: \n988: ### 基本使用\n989: \n990: ```python\n991: from agentcube.services.docker_service import DockerService\n992: from pathlib import Path\n993: \n994: # 创建服务实例\n995: docker_service = DockerService(verbose=True)\n996: \n997: # 检查 Docker 可用性\n998: if not docker_service.check_docker_available():\n999:     print(\"Docker is not available\")\n1000:     exit(1)\n1001: \n1002: # 构建镜像\n1003: build_result = docker_service.build_image(\n1004:     dockerfile_path=Path(\"Dockerfile\"),\n1005:     context_path=Path(\".\"),\n1006:     image_name=\"myagent\",\n1007:     tag=\"v1.0.0\"\n1008: )\n1009: \n1010: print(f\"Built image: {build_result['image_name']}\")\n1011: print(f\"Image ID: {build_result['image_id']}\")\n1012: print(f\"Size: {build_result['image_size']}\")\n1013: \n1014: # 推送到私有仓库\n1015: push_result = docker_service.push_image(\n1016:     image_name=\"myagent:v1.0.0\",\n1017:     registry_url=\"registry.example.com/username\",\n1018:     username=\"myuser\",\n1019:     password=\"mypassword\"\n1020: )\n1021: \n1022: print(f\"Pushed: {push_result['pushed_image']}\")\n1023: ```\n1024: \n1025: ### 在 BuildRuntime 中使用\n1026: \n1027: ```python\n1028: class BuildRuntime:\n1029:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None:\n1030:         self.verbose = verbose\n1031:         self.docker_service = DockerService(verbose=verbose)\n1032: \n1033:     def build(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n1034:         \"\"\"Build agent Docker image.\"\"\"\n1035:         metadata = self._load_metadata(workspace_path)\n1036: \n1037:         build_result = self.docker_service.build_image(\n1038:             dockerfile_path=workspace_path / \"Dockerfile\",\n1039:             context_path=workspace_path,\n1040:             image_name=metadata.agent_name,\n1041:             tag=metadata.version or \"latest\",\n1042:             build_args=options.get(\"build_args\")\n1043:         )\n1044: \n1045:         return build_result\n1046: ```\n1047: \n1048: ### 在 PublishRuntime 中使用\n1049: \n1050: ```python\n1051: class PublishRuntime:\n1052:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None:\n1053:         self.verbose = verbose\n1054:         self.docker_service = DockerService(verbose=verbose)\n1055:         self.provider = provider\n1056: \n1057:     def publish(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n1058:         \"\"\"Publish agent to registry or Kubernetes.\"\"\"\n1059:         metadata = self._load_metadata(workspace_path)\n1060: \n1061:         # 准备镜像\n1062:         image_name = self._prepare_image(workspace_path, metadata, options)\n1063: \n1064:         # 推送镜像\n1065:         push_result = self.docker_service.push_image(\n1066:             image_name=image_name,\n1067:             registry_url=options.get(\"registry_url\"),\n1068:             username=options.get(\"image_username\"),\n1069:             password=options.get(\"image_password\")\n1070:         )\n1071: \n1072:         # 更新元数据\n1073:         metadata.image = {\n1074:             \"name\": push_result[\"pushed_image\"],\n1075:             \"pushed_at\": push_result[\"push_time\"]\n1076:         }\n1077:         self._save_metadata(workspace_path, metadata)\n1078: \n1079:         return push_result\n1080: ```\n1081: \n1082: ## 与其他组件的交互\n1083: \n1084: ### BuildRuntime 使用\n1085: \n1086: | BuildRuntime → DockerService | 说明 |\n1087: |----------------------------|------|\n1088: | `check_docker_available()` | 构建前检查 Docker 可用性 |\n1089: | `build_image()` | 构建代理镜像 |\n1090: | `get_image_info()` | 获取构建结果信息 |\n1091: | `remove_image()` | 清理失败构建的镜像 |\n1092: \n1093: ### PublishRuntime 使用\n1094: \n1095: | PublishRuntime → DockerService | 说明 |\n1096: |-------------------------------|------|\n1097: | `check_docker_available()` | 推送前检查 Docker 可用性 |\n1098: | `push_image()` | 推送镜像到仓库 |\n1099: | `_tag_image_sdk()` | 重新标记镜像用于推送 |\n1100: | `_docker_login_sdk()` | 认证私有仓库 |\n1101: \n1102: ### 与 CLI 的集成\n1103: \n1104: ```python\n1105: # agentcube/cli/main.py\n1106: def build(\n1107:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\"),\n1108:     proxy: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"-p\", \"--proxy\"),\n1109:     cloud_provider: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--cloud-provider\"),\n1110:     output: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--output\"),\n1111:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\"),\n1112: ) -> None:\n1113:     \"\"\"Build agent Docker image.\"\"\"\n1114:     try:\n1115:         runtime = BuildRuntime(verbose=verbose)\n1116:         result = runtime.build(\n1117:             workspace_path=Path(workspace),\n1118:             proxy=proxy,\n1119:             cloud_provider=cloud_provider,\n1120:             output_path=output\n1121:         )\n1122: \n1123:         console.print(f\"✓ Built {result['image_name']}\")\n1124:         console.print(f\"  Image ID: {result['image_id']}\")\n1125:         console.print(f\"  Size: {result['image_size']}\")\n1126:     except Exception as e:\n1127:         _handle_error(e, \"build\", verbose)\n1128: ```\n1129: \n1130: ## 未来增强\n1131: \n1132: ### 短期增强（1-2 个月）\n1133: \n1134: 1. **超时支持**: 为 `build_image()` 和 `push_image()` 添加超时参数\n1135: 2. **进度回调**: 支持进度回调函数，用于 UI 更新\n1136: 3. **多架构构建**: 支持 `--platform` 参数构建多架构镜像\n1137: 4. **构建缓存优化**: 支持 `--cache-from` 和 `--cache-to` 参数\n1138: \n1139: ### 中期增强（3-6 个月）\n1140: \n1141: 1. **并行构建**: 支持并行构建多个镜像\n1142: 2. **构建历史**: 维护构建历史记录\n1143: 3. **镜像分析**: 添加镜像层分析和优化建议\n1144: 4. **安全扫描**: 集成镜像安全扫描（如 Trivy）\n1145: \n1146: ### 长期增强（6-12 个月）\n1147: \n1148: 1. **分布式构建**: 支持远程构建集群\n1149: 2. **构建缓存服务**: 集中式构建缓存服务\n1150: 3. **镜像签名**: 支持镜像签名和验证\n1151: 4. **CI/CD 集成**: 提供更深入的 CI/CD 系统集成\n1152: \n1153: ## 故障排查\n1154: \n1155: ### 常见问题\n1156: \n1157: **问题 1: Docker daemon 不可用**\n1158: \n1159: ```\n1160: RuntimeError: Docker is not available or not running\n1161: ```\n1162: \n1163: **解决方案**:\n1164: 1. 检查 Docker daemon 是否运行：`docker ps`\n1165: 2. 检查 `DOCKER_HOST` 环境变量\n1166: 3. 检查 Docker 服务状态：`sudo systemctl status docker`\n1167: 4. 重启 Docker 服务：`sudo systemctl restart docker`\n1168: \n1169: **问题 2: 构建失败 - 权限错误**\n1170: \n1171: ```\n1172: PermissionError: [Errno 13] Permission denied: 'Dockerfile'\n1173: ```\n1174: \n1175: **解决方案**:\n1176: 1. 检查文件权限：`ls -la Dockerfile`\n1177: 2. 确保当前用户有读取权限\n1178: 3. 检查 Docker 用户组权限\n1179: \n1180: **问题 3: 推送失败 - 认证错误**\n1181: \n1182: ```\n1183: RuntimeError: Failed to log in to Docker registry: unauthorized\n1184: ```\n1185: \n1186: **解决方案**:\n1187: 1. 验证用户名和密码\n1188: 2. 检查仓库 URL 是否正确\n1189: 3. 确认仓库权限设置\n1190: 4. 尝试手动登录：`docker login registry.example.com`\n1191: \n1192: **问题 4: 推送失败 - 网络错误**\n1193: \n1194: ```\n1195: RuntimeError: Failed to push Docker image: connection timeout\n1196: ```\n1197: \n1198: **解决方案**:\n1199: 1. 检查网络连接\n1200: 2. 配置代理（如适用）\n1201: 3. 检查防火墙设置\n1202: 4. 增加超时时间\n1203: \n1204: ### 调试技巧\n1205: \n1206: **启用详细日志**\n1207: \n1208: ```python\n1209: docker_service = DockerService(verbose=True)\n1210: ```\n1211: \n1212: **检查 Docker 日志**\n1213: \n1214: ```bash\n1215: # Linux\n1216: sudo journalctl -u docker -f\n1217: \n1218: # macOS (Docker Desktop)\n1219: open /Applications/Docker.app\n1220: \n1221: # Windows\n1222: Get-Service docker\n1223: ```\n1224: \n1225: **验证 Docker 连接**\n1226: \n1227: ```python\n1228: service = DockerService()\n1229: if service.check_docker_available():\n1230:     print(\"Docker is available\")\n1231: else:\n1232:     print(\"Docker is not available\")\n1233: ```\n1234: \n1235: ## 总结\n1236: \n1237: DockerService 是 AgentCube CLI 的核心组件之一，为构建和发布工作流提供了统一的 Docker 操作接口。其主要特点包括：\n1238: \n1239: 1. **简洁的 API**: 封装 Docker SDK 复杂性，提供简单易用的接口\n1240: 2. **完善的错误处理**: 统一的错误处理策略，清晰的错误信息\n1241: 3. **安全设计**: 妥善处理敏感信息，验证输入参数\n1242: 4. **可观测性**: 支持详细日志模式，便于调试\n1243: 5. **可测试性**: 完善的单元测试和集成测试\n1244: 6. **可扩展性**: 清晰的架构，便于未来功能增强\n1245: \n1246: 通过 DockerService，BuildRuntime 和 PublishRuntime 可以专注于业务逻辑，而将 Docker 操作的复杂性委托给专门的服务层。这种设计提高了代码的可维护性、可测试性和可重用性。\n\n(End of file - total 1246 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-024 — DockerService 封装 (DockerService Encapsulation)\n\n## 模块信息\n\n- **模块**: `cmd/cli`\n- **语言**: Python\n- **规模**: M\n- **关联需求**: AR-024\n\n## 架构概述\n\n### 设计目标\n\nDockerService 是一个封装了 Docker SDK 操作的服务类，为 AgentCube CLI 的构建和发布工作流提供统一的 Docker 接口。该服务封装了 Docker SDK 的复杂性，提供了简洁的高级 API 用于镜像构建、推送、标记和管理等操作，同时提供完善的错误处理、日志记录和输入验证机制。\n\n### 核心组件\n\n```\nagentcube/services/\n├── docker_service.py         # DockerService 主要实现","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-024/design.md","time":{"start":1775871125574,"end":1775871125598}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775871125604,"sessionID":"ses_285d570caffeupuoMbNOk82vM3","part":{"id":"prt_d7a2ae545001fLZWIN2g9HLfFd","messageID":"msg_d7a2ad606001naI1skHUV4yTIn","sessionID":"ses_285d570caffeupuoMbNOk82vM3","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-e57fa8802ed1488781c3227bd0bdb086","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-024/delta-spec.md","limit":500},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-024/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Specification: AR-024 — DockerService 封装\n2: \n3: ## Module: `cmd/cli`\n4: \n5: ## Language: Python\n6: \n7: ## Size: M\n8: \n9: ## Delta Overview\n10: \n11: Enhance and formalize the `DockerService` class to provide a robust, well-encapsulated interface for Docker operations including image building, pushing, tagging, and management. This specification defines the complete behavior, error handling, and testing requirements for the Docker service layer used by the AgentCube CLI's build and publish workflows.\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## REQ-001: DockerService initialization and configuration\n16: \n17: ### Requirement: Service initialization with verbose logging\n18: \n19: System SHALL provide a `DockerService` class that initializes with optional verbose logging and configures the Docker client properly.\n20: \n21: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n22: - Constructor accepts optional verbose boolean parameter\n23: - Stores verbose flag for use in logging operations\n24: - Initializes Docker client using `docker.from_env()`\n25: - Handles Docker client initialization failures gracefully\n26: \n27: **Scenarios:**\n28: \n29: #### Scenario 1.1: Initialize with verbose logging enabled\n30: - **GIVEN** a developer creates a `DockerService` instance with `verbose=True`\n31: - **WHEN** the service initializes\n32: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n33:   - Store the verbose flag as an instance variable\n34:   - Initialize the Docker client using `docker.from_env()`\n35:   - Log initialization message if verbose is enabled\n36: \n37: #### Scenario 1.2: Initialize with verbose logging disabled\n38: - **GIVEN** a developer creates a `DockerService` instance with `verbose=False` or no verbose parameter\n39: - **WHEN** the service initializes\n40: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n41:   - Store `verbose=False` as an instance variable\n42:   - Initialize the Docker client using `docker.from_env()`\n43:   - NOT log initialization message\n44: \n45: #### Scenario 1.3: Docker client initialization failure\n46: - **GIVEN** Docker daemon is not running or not installed\n47: - **WHEN** `DockerService.__init__()` attempts to initialize the client\n48: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n49:   - Raise an appropriate exception (e.g., `RuntimeError` or `docker.errors.DockerException`)\n50:   - Include a descriptive message about Docker availability\n51: \n52: ---\n53: \n54: ## REQ-002: Docker availability checking\n55: \n56: ### Requirement: Check Docker daemon availability\n57: \n58: System SHALL provide a method to check if Docker daemon is available and running.\n59: \n60: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n61: - Method returns boolean indicating Docker availability\n62: - Logs availability check result when verbose is enabled\n63: - Handles connection failures gracefully\n64: \n65: **Scenarios:**\n66: \n67: #### Scenario 2.1: Docker daemon is available\n68: - **GIVEN** Docker daemon is running and accessible\n69: - **WHEN** `check_docker_available()` is called\n70: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n71:   - Attempt to connect to Docker daemon\n72:   - Return `True` if connection succeeds\n73:   - Log \"Docker is available\" if verbose is enabled\n74: \n75: #### Scenario 2.2: Docker daemon is not available\n76: - **GIVEN** Docker daemon is not running or not installed\n77: - **WHEN** `check_docker_available()` is called\n78: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n79:   - Attempt to connect to Docker daemon\n80:   - Return `False` if connection fails\n81:   - Log a warning message if verbose is enabled\n82:   - NOT raise an exception (return gracefully)\n83: \n84: #### Scenario 2.3: Docker client not initialized\n85: - **GIVEN** the DockerService instance was not properly initialized\n86: - **WHEN** `check_docker_available()` is called\n87: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n88:   - Return `False`\n89:   - Log appropriate error message if verbose is enabled\n90: \n91: ---\n92: \n93: ## REQ-003: Docker image building\n94: \n95: ### Requirement: Build Docker images from Dockerfiles\n96: \n97: System SHALL provide a method to build Docker images with configurable options.\n98: \n99: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n100: - Accepts dockerfile path, context path, image name, and optional tag\n101: - Supports build arguments for proxy configuration\n102: - Streams build logs in real-time\n103: - Returns detailed build result information\n104: - Handles build failures with descriptive errors\n105: \n106: **Scenarios:**\n107: \n108: #### Scenario 3.1: Build image with default tag\n109: - **GIVEN** a valid Dockerfile at `/path/to/Dockerfile`\n110: - **AND** a build context directory at `/path/to/context`\n111: - **WHEN** `build_image(dockerfile_path=\"/path/to/Dockerfile\", context_path=\"/path/to/context\", image_name=\"myimage\")` is called\n112: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n113:   - Build the image with tag `\"latest\"` by default\n114:   - Return a dict containing:\n115:     - `image_name`: `\"myimage:latest\"`\n116:     - `image_id`: the SHA256 hash of the built image\n117:     - `image_size`: human-readable size string\n118:     - `build_time`: ISO 8601 timestamp\n119: \n120: #### Scenario 3.2: Build image with custom tag\n121: - **GIVEN** a valid Dockerfile and build context\n122: - **WHEN** `build_image(..., tag=\"v1.0.0\")` is called\n123: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n124:   - Build the image with tag `\"v1.0.0\"`\n125:   - Return result with `image_name: \"myimage:v1.0.0\"`\n126: \n127: #### Scenario 3.3: Build image with build arguments\n128: - **GIVEN** a Dockerfile that expects build arguments\n129: - **WHEN** `build_image(..., build_args={\"HTTP_PROXY\": \"http://proxy.example.com:8080\", \"HTTPS_PROXY\": \"https://proxy.example.com:8080\"})` is called\n130: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n131:   - Pass the build arguments to Docker during build\n132:   - Use them for dependency resolution during the build process\n133: \n134: #### Scenario 3.4: Build success with verbose logging\n135: - **GIVEN** `verbose=True` when creating `DockerService`\n136: - **WHEN** `build_image()` successfully completes\n137: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n138:   - Log each build step as it progresses\n139:   - Log final success message with image details\n140: \n141: #### Scenario 3.5: Build failure with invalid Dockerfile\n142: - **GIVEN** an invalid Dockerfile with syntax errors\n143: - **WHEN** `build_image()` is called\n144: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n145:   - Raise an appropriate exception (e.g., `BuildError` or `docker.errors.BuildError`)\n146:   - Include descriptive error message about the build failure\n147:   - Log build error details if verbose is enabled\n148: \n149: #### Scenario 3.6: Build failure with missing Dockerfile\n150: - **GIVEN** a dockerfile_path that does not exist\n151: - **WHEN** `build_image()` is called\n152: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n153:   - Raise a `FileNotFoundError` or `ValueError`\n154:   - Include the missing file path in the error message\n155: \n156: #### Scenario 3.7: Build failure with missing context directory\n157: - **GIVEN** a context_path that does not exist\n158: - **WHEN** `build_image()` is called\n159: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n160:   - Raise a `FileNotFoundError` or `ValueError`\n161:   - Include the missing directory path in the error message\n162: \n163: ---\n164: \n165: ## REQ-004: Docker image information retrieval\n166: \n167: ### Requirement: Retrieve detailed image information\n168: \n169: System SHALL provide methods to retrieve metadata about Docker images.\n170: \n171: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n172: - Returns image ID, size, creation time, and tags\n173: - Formats size in human-readable format\n174: - Handles non-existent images appropriately\n175: \n176: **Scenarios:**\n177: \n178: #### Scenario 4.1: Get info for existing image\n179: - **GIVEN** a Docker image exists locally with name `\"myimage:latest\"`\n180: - **WHEN** `get_image_info(\"myimage:latest\")` is called\n181: - **THEN** the system SHALL return a dict containing:\n182:   - `image_id`: the SHA256 hash of the image\n183:   - `image_size`: human-readable format (e.g., \"2.0 GB\" or \"2 GiB\")\n184:   - `created`: ISO 8601 timestamp\n185:   - `tags`: list of tags associated with the image\n186: \n187: #### Scenario 4.2: Format size in human-readable format\n188: - **GIVEN** an image size of 2147483648 bytes (2 GB)\n189: - **WHEN** the system formats the size\n190: - **THEN** the result SHALL be one of:\n191:   - `\"2.0 GB\"` (decimal format)\n192:   - `\"2.0 GiB\"` (binary format)\n193:   - Consistent format must be used throughout\n194: \n195: #### Scenario 4.3: Get info for image without tag (defaults to latest)\n196: - **GIVEN** a Docker image exists with name `\"myimage\"` and tag `\"latest\"`\n197: - **WHEN** `get_image_info(\"myimage\")` is called (without tag)\n198: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n199:   - Look for the `\"latest\"` tag\n200:   - Return information for `myimage:latest`\n201: \n202: #### Scenario 4.4: Get info for non-existent image\n203: - **GIVEN** an image name `\"nonexistent:latest\"` that does not exist locally\n204: - **WHEN** `get_image_info(\"nonexistent:latest\")` is called\n205: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n206:   - Raise an appropriate exception (e.g., `ImageNotFoundError`)\n207:   - Include descriptive message indicating the image was not found\n208: \n209: #### Scenario 4.5: Get info with verbose logging\n210: - **GIVEN** `verbose=True` when creating `DockerService`\n211: - **WHEN** `get_image_info()` successfully retrieves image information\n212: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n213:   - Log the retrieval operation\n214:   - Log the image details\n215: \n216: ---\n217: \n218: ## REQ-005: Docker image pushing to registry\n219: \n220: ### Requirement: Push images to container registries\n221: \n222: System SHALL provide a method to push Docker images to container registries with optional authentication.\n223: \n224: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n225: - Supports public and private registries\n226: - Handles authentication when credentials provided\n227: - Re-tags images for registry push when needed\n228: - Streams push progress in real-time\n229: - Returns push result information\n230: \n231: **Scenarios:**\n232: \n233: #### Scenario 5.1: Push image without authentication to public registry\n234: - **GIVEN** a local image `\"myimage:latest\"` exists\n235: - **AND** a public registry URL `\"registry.example.com/username\"`\n236: - **WHEN** `push_image(image_name=\"myimage\", registry_url=\"registry.example.com/username\")` is called\n237: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n238:   - Re-tag the image to `\"registry.example.com/username/myimage:latest\"`\n239:   - Push the image to the registry without authentication\n240:   - Return a dict containing:\n241:     - `pushed_image`: `\"registry.example.com/username/myimage:latest\"`\n242:     - `push_time`: ISO 8601 timestamp\n243: \n244: #### Scenario 5.2: Push image with authentication to private registry\n245: - **GIVEN** a local image exists\n246: - **AND** a private registry requiring credentials\n247: - **WHEN** `push_image(image_name=\"myimage\", registry_url=\"registry.example.com/username\", username=\"myuser\", password=\"mypass\")` is called\n248: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n249:   - Authenticate with the registry using provided credentials\n250:   - Re-tag the image for the registry\n251:   - Push the authenticated image\n252:   - Return push result information\n253: \n254: #### Scenario 5.3: Push image with tag specification\n255: - **GIVEN** a local image `\"myimage:v1.0.0\"` exists\n256: - **WHEN** `push_image(image_name=\"myimage:v1.0.0\", registry_url=\"registry.example.com/username\")` is called\n257: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n258:   - Re-tag to `\"registry.example.com/username/myimage:v1.0.0\"`\n259:   - Push the specific tagged version\n260: \n261: #### Scenario 5.4: Push with verbose logging\n262: - **GIVEN** `verbose=True` when creating `DockerService`\n263: - **WHEN** `push_image()` is called\n264: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n265:   - Log authentication step if applicable\n266:   - Log re-tagging operation\n267:   - Stream and log push progress for each layer\n268: \n269: #### Scenario 5.5: Push failure due to authentication error\n270: - **GIVEN** invalid credentials for a private registry\n271: - **WHEN** `push_image()` attempts to authenticate and push\n272: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n273:   - Raise an authentication exception\n274:   - Include descriptive error message about authentication failure\n275:   - NOT store or log the password\n276: \n277: #### Scenario 5.6: Push failure due to network issues\n278: - **GIVEN** network connectivity issues or unreachable registry\n279: - **WHEN** `push_image()` is called\n280: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n281:   - Raise a network-related exception\n282:   - Include descriptive error message about the connection failure\n283: \n284: #### Scenario 5.7: Push failure due to non-existent local image\n285: - **GIVEN** an image name that does not exist locally\n286: - **WHEN** `push_image()` is called\n287: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n288:   - Raise an exception indicating the image was not found\n289:   - Include the image name in the error message\n290: \n291: ---\n292: \n293: ## REQ-006: Docker image removal\n294: \n295: ### Requirement: Remove Docker images from local daemon\n296: \n297: System SHALL provide a method to remove Docker images from the local Docker daemon.\n298: \n299: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n300: - Removes existing images successfully\n301: - Returns boolean indicating success/failure\n302: - Handles non-existent images gracefully\n303: - Supports force removal option\n304: \n305: **Scenarios:**\n306: \n307: #### Scenario 6.1: Remove existing image\n308: - **GIVEN** a Docker image `\"myimage:latest\"` exists locally\n309: - **WHEN** `remove_image(\"myimage:latest\")` is called\n310: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n311:   - Remove the image from local Docker daemon\n312:   - Return `True`\n313:   - Log removal operation if verbose is enabled\n314: \n315: #### Scenario 6.2: Remove non-existent image\n316: - **GIVEN** an image name `\"nonexistent:latest\"` that does not exist locally\n317: - **WHEN** `remove_image(\"nonexistent:latest\")` is called\n318: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n319:   - Return `False`\n320:   - Log a warning message if verbose is enabled\n321:   - NOT raise an exception\n322: \n323: #### Scenario 6.3: Force remove image in use\n324: - **GIVEN** an image that has dependent containers or is in use\n325: - **WHEN** `remove_image(\"myimage:latest\", force=True)` is called\n326: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n327:   - Attempt to force-remove the image\n328:   - Return `True` if successful\n329:   - Return `False` if removal still fails\n330:   - Log the operation if verbose is enabled\n331: \n332: #### Scenario 6.4: Remove image without force (fails when in use)\n333: - **GIVEN** an image that has dependent containers\n334: - **WHEN** `remove_image(\"myimage:latest\")` is called without force option\n335: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n336:   - Return `False`\n337:   - Log a warning message if verbose is enabled\n338:   - NOT raise an exception\n339: \n340: ---\n341: \n342: ## REQ-007: Docker registry authentication\n343: \n344: ### Requirement: Authenticate with Docker registries\n345: \n346: System SHALL provide methods to authenticate with Docker registries using username/password credentials.\n347: \n348: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n349: - Authenticates with specified registry URL\n350: - Supports Docker Hub as default registry\n351: - Handles authentication failures appropriately\n352: - Does not store passwords in logs\n353: \n354: **Scenarios:**\n355: \n356: #### Scenario 7.1: Login to private registry\n357: - **GIVEN** valid credentials for a private registry\n358: - **WHEN** `_docker_login_sdk(registry_url=\"registry.example.com\", username=\"myuser\", password=\"mypass\")` is called\n359: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n360:   - Use Docker SDK to authenticate with the specified registry\n361:   - Return success or raise exception on failure\n362:   - NOT log or store the password\n363: \n364: #### Scenario 7.2: Login to Docker Hub (default registry)\n365: - **GIVEN** valid Docker Hub credentials\n366: - **WHEN** `_docker_login_sdk(registry_url=None, username=\"myuser\", password=\"mypass\")` is called\n367: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n368:   - Authenticate with Docker Hub (default registry)\n369:   - Return success or raise exception on failure\n370: \n371: #### Scenario 7.3: Authentication failure with invalid credentials\n372: - **GIVEN** invalid credentials for a registry\n373: - **WHEN** `_docker_login_sdk()` is called with invalid credentials\n374: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n375:   - Raise an authentication exception\n376:   - Include descriptive error message about authentication failure\n377: \n378: #### Scenario 7.4: Authentication failure with unreachable registry\n379: - **GIVEN** credentials but registry is unreachable\n380: - **WHEN** `_docker_login_sdk()` is called\n381: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n382:   - Raise a network-related exception\n383:   - Include descriptive error message about connection failure\n384: \n385: ---\n386: \n387: ## REQ-008: Docker image tagging\n388: \n389: ### Requirement: Tag Docker images for registry\n390: \n391: System SHALL provide methods to tag Docker images with new names or repository paths.\n392: \n393: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n394: - Tags images for registry push\n395: - Handles multiple tags\n396: - Validates source image exists\n397: - Handles tagging failures\n398: \n399: **Scenarios:**\n400: \n401: #### Scenario 8.1: Tag image for registry\n402: - **GIVEN** a local image `\"myimage:latest\"` exists\n403: - **WHEN** `_tag_image_sdk(source_image=\"myimage:latest\", target_image=\"registry.example.com/username/myimage:v1.0\")` is called\n404: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n405:   - Create a new tag for the image\n406:   - Point to the specified registry path\n407:   - Return success\n408: \n409: #### Scenario 8.2: Tag non-existent source image\n410: - **GIVEN** a source image that does not exist\n411: - **WHEN** `_tag_image_sdk(source_image=\"nonexistent:latest\", target_image=\"registry.example.com/username/myimage:v1.0\")` is called\n412: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n413:   - Raise an exception with descriptive message\n414:   - Indicate that the source image was not found\n415: \n416: #### Scenario 8.3: Tag image with invalid target format\n417: - **GIVEN** a valid source image\n418: - **WHEN** `_tag_image_sdk(source_image=\"myimage:latest\", target_image=\"invalid:image:name:format\")` is called\n419: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n420:   - Raise an exception or return failure\n421:   - Indicate invalid image name format\n422: \n423: ---\n424: \n425: ## REQ-009: Verbose logging and error reporting\n426: \n427: ### Requirement: Consistent verbose logging across operations\n428: \n429: System SHALL provide consistent verbose logging and meaningful error messages for all Docker operations.\n430: \n431: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n432: - Logs operation progress when verbose is enabled\n433: - Provides descriptive error messages for all failures\n434: - Uses appropriate log levels (info, warning, error)\n435: - Does not expose sensitive information in logs\n436: \n437: **Scenarios:**\n438: \n439: #### Scenario 9.1: Verbose logging during build\n440: - **GIVEN** `verbose=True` when creating `DockerService`\n441: - **WHEN** `build_image()` is called\n442: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n443:   - Log build start message with image name\n444:   - Log each build step as it progresses\n445:   - Log final success message with image ID and size\n446:   - Log build error details if build fails\n447: \n448: #### Scenario 9.2: Verbose logging during push\n449: - **GIVEN** `verbose=True` and an image push operation\n450: - **WHEN** `push_image()` is called\n451: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n452:   - Log authentication step (without password)\n453:   - Log re-tagging operation\n454:   - Log push progress for each layer being transferred\n455:   - Log final success message with pushed image name\n456: \n457: #### Scenario 9.3: Descriptive error messages\n458: - **GIVEN** any Docker operation fails\n459: - **WHEN** an exception is raised\n460: - **THEN** the exception message SHALL include:\n461:   - The operation that failed (build, push, remove, etc.)\n462:   - The image name involved\n463:   - The root cause of the failure\n464: \n465: #### Scenario 9.4: No sensitive information in logs\n466: - **GIVEN** an operation involving credentials (e.g., push with password)\n467: - **WHEN** verbose logging is enabled\n468: - **THEN** the logs SHALL:\n469:   - NOT contain the password in plain text\n470:   - Use placeholders like `******` or `[REDACTED]` for sensitive values\n471: \n472: #### Scenario 9.5: Silent operation without verbose logging\n473: - **GIVEN** `verbose=False` when creating `DockerService`\n474: - **WHEN** any Docker operation is called\n475: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n476:   - NOT log operation progress\n477:   - Only raise exceptions on failures (not log them)\n478: \n479: ---\n480: \n481: ## REQ-010: Input validation and parameter handling\n482: \n483: ### Requirement: Validate all input parameters\n484: \n485: System SHALL validate all input parameters before initiating Docker operations.\n486: \n487: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n488: - Validates file paths exist\n489: - Validates parameter types and formats\n490: - Provides clear error messages for invalid inputs\n491: - Handles edge cases gracefully\n492: \n493: **Scenarios:**\n494: \n495: #### Scenario 10.1: Validate dockerfile_path exists\n496: - **GIVEN** a dockerfile_path that does not exist\n497: - **WHEN** `build_image()` is called\n498: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n499:   - Raise `FileNotFoundError` or `ValueError`\n500:   - Include the missing file path in the error message\n\n(Showing lines 1-500 of 971. Use offset=501 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Specification: AR-024 — DockerService 封装\n\n## Module: `cmd/cli`\n\n## Language: Python\n\n## Size: M\n\n## Delta Overview\n\nEnhance and formalize the `DockerService` class to provide a robust, well-encapsulated interface for Docker operations including image building, pushing, tagging, and management. This specification defines the complete behavior, error handling, and testing requirements for the Docker service layer used by the AgentCube CLI's build and publish workflows.\n\n---\n\n## REQ-001: DockerService initialization and configuration\n\n### Requirement: Service initialization with verbose logging\n\nSystem SHALL provide a `DockerService` class that initializes with optional verbose logging and configures the Docker client properly.\n","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-024/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775871125580,"end":1775871125602}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775871125617,"sessionID":"ses_285d570caffeupuoMbNOk82vM3","part":{"id":"prt_d7a2ae8180014HXTB8V8nfIR1D","messageID":"msg_d7a2ad606001naI1skHUV4yTIn","sessionID":"ses_285d570caffeupuoMbNOk82vM3","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-6f57190958254491a62b25c84b34c267","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: \"\"\"Service for Docker operations.\"\"\"\n2: \n3: import logging\n4: import time\n5: from pathlib import Path\n6: from typing import Any, Dict, Optional\n7: \n8: import docker\n9: from docker.errors import DockerException\n10: \n11: \n12: logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n13: \n14: \n15: class DockerService:\n16:     \"\"\"Service for Docker operations.\"\"\"\n17: \n18:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None:\n19:         \"\"\"Initialize the Docker service.\"\"\"\n20:         self.verbose = verbose\n21:         if verbose:\n22:             logging.basicConfig(level=logging.DEBUG)\n23:         self._client: Optional[docker.DockerClient] = None\n24: \n25:     @property\n26:     def client(self) -> docker.DockerClient:\n27:         \"\"\"Get or create Docker client.\"\"\"\n28:         if self._client is None:\n29:             self._client = docker.from_env()\n30:         return self._client\n31: \n32:     def check_docker_available(self) -> bool:\n33:         \"\"\"Check if Docker is available and running.\"\"\"\n34:         try:\n35:             self.client.ping()\n36:             return True\n37:         except DockerException as e:\n38:             logger.warning(f\"Docker not available: {e}\")\n39:             return False\n40: \n41:     def build_image(\n42:         self,\n43:         dockerfile_path: Path,\n44:         context_path: Path,\n45:         image_name: str,\n46:         tag: str = \"latest\",\n47:         build_args: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n48:     ) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n49:         \"\"\"Build a Docker image.\"\"\"\n50:         if not self.check_docker_available():\n51:             raise RuntimeError(\"Docker is not available or not running\")\n52: \n53:         logger.info(f\"Building image {image_name}:{tag} from {dockerfile_path}\")\n54:         full_image_name = f\"{image_name}:{tag}\"\n55: \n56:         try:\n57:             image, build_logs = self.client.images.build(\n58:                 path=str(context_path),\n59:                 dockerfile=str(dockerfile_path),\n60:                 tag=full_image_name,\n61:                 buildargs=build_args,\n62:                 rm=True,\n63:                 forcerm=True,\n64:             )\n65: \n66:             image_info = self.get_image_info(full_image_name)\n67:             image_info[\"build_time\"] = time.time()\n68: \n69:             return image_info\n70: \n71:         except DockerException as e:\n72:             raise RuntimeError(f\"Failed to build Docker image: {e}\") from e\n73: \n74:     def get_image_info(self, image_name: str) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n75:         \"\"\"Get information about a Docker image.\"\"\"\n76:         try:\n77:             image = self.client.images.get(image_name)\n78:             attrs = image.attrs\n79: \n80:             image_id = attrs[\"Id\"].split(\":\")[-1][:12]\n81:             size_bytes = attrs.get(\"Size\", 0)\n82: \n83:             return {\n84:                 \"image_name\": image_name,\n85:                 \"image_id\": image_id,\n86:                 \"image_size\": self._format_size(size_bytes),\n87:                 \"size_bytes\": size_bytes,\n88:             }\n89: \n90:         except DockerException as e:\n91:             logger.warning(f\"Failed to get image info for {image_name}: {e}\")\n92:             return {}\n93: \n94:     def _format_size(self, size_bytes: int) -> str:\n95:         \"\"\"Format size in human-readable format.\"\"\"\n96:         size = float(size_bytes)\n97:         for unit in [\"B\", \"KB\", \"MB\", \"GB\"]:\n98:             if size < 1024:\n99:                 return f\"{size:.2f} {unit}\"\n100:             size /= 1024\n101:         return f\"{size:.2f} TB\"\n102: \n103:     def push_image(\n104:         self,\n105:         image_name: str,\n106:         registry_url: Optional[str] = None,\n107:         username: Optional[str] = None,\n108:         password: Optional[str] = None,\n109:     ) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n110:         \"\"\"Push a Docker image to a registry.\"\"\"\n111:         if not self.check_docker_available():\n112:             raise RuntimeError(\"Docker is not available or not running\")\n113: \n114:         target_image = image_name\n115:         if registry_url:\n116:             target_image = f\"{registry_url}/{image_name}\"\n117:             self._tag_image_sdk(image_name, target_image)\n118: \n119:         if username and password:\n120:             self._docker_login_sdk(registry_url, username, password)\n121: \n122:         logger.info(f\"Pushing image {target_image}\")\n123: \n124:         try:\n125:             push_logs = self.client.images.push(target_image, stream=True, decode=True)\n126: \n127:             for line in push_logs:\n128:                 if \"error\" in line:\n129:                     raise RuntimeError(f\"Failed to push image: {line['error']}\")\n130:                 if self.verbose:\n131:                     logger.debug(f\"Push log: {line}\")\n132: \n133:             return {\n134:                 \"pushed_image\": target_image,\n135:                 \"push_time\": str(time.time()),\n136:             }\n137: \n138:         except DockerException as e:\n139:             raise RuntimeError(f\"Failed to push Docker image: {e}\") from e\n140: \n141:     def _docker_login_sdk(self, registry: Optional[str], username: str, password: str) -> None:\n142:         \"\"\"Log in to Docker registry.\"\"\"\n143:         try:\n144:             self.client.login(username=username, password=password, registry=registry)\n145:             logger.info(f\"Successfully logged in to registry: {registry or 'default'}\")\n146:         except DockerException as e:\n147:             raise RuntimeError(f\"Failed to log in to Docker registry: {e}\") from e\n148: \n149:     def _tag_image_sdk(self, source_image: str, target_image: str) -> None:\n150:         \"\"\"Tag a Docker image.\"\"\"\n151:         try:\n152:             image = self.client.images.get(source_image)\n153:             image.tag(target_image, force=True)\n154:             logger.info(f\"Tagged {source_image} as {target_image}\")\n155:         except DockerException as e:\n156:             raise RuntimeError(f\"Failed to tag Docker image: {e}\") from e\n157: \n158:     def remove_image(self, image_name: str) -> bool:\n159:         \"\"\"Remove a Docker image.\"\"\"\n160:         try:\n161:             self.client.images.remove(image_name, force=True)\n162:             logger.info(f\"Removed image {image_name}\")\n163:             return True\n164:         except DockerException as e:\n165:             logger.warning(f\"Failed to remove image {image_name}: {e}\")\n166:             return False\n\n(End of file - total 166 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"\"\"\"Service for Docker operations.\"\"\"\n\nimport logging\nimport time\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Any, Dict, Optional\n\nimport docker\nfrom docker.errors import DockerException\n\n\nlogger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n\n\nclass DockerService:\n    \"\"\"Service for Docker operations.\"\"\"\n\n    def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Initialize the Docker service.\"\"\"\n        self.verbose = verbose","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_202